law.catch_line: Power of Attorney General not to affect powers or duties of local officers.
law.text: Except as provided in KRS 15.190 to 15.240, the powers and duties conferred upon or required of the Attorney General by KRS 15.190 to 15.240 shall not be construed to deprive prosecuting attorneys of any of their authority in respect to criminal prosecutions, or relieve them from any of their duties to enforce the criminal laws of the Commonwealth.
law.history: Amended 1966 Ky. Acts ch. 255, sec. 8. -- Created 1964 Ky. Acts ch. 28, sec. 4.
